<div id="content">
	<h1>Athena SWAN</h1>
<h2>What is Athena SWAN?</h2>
<p><a title="Athena SWAN" href="http://www.ecu.ac.uk/equality-charter-marks/athena-swan/" target="_blank">Athena SWAN</a> is an initiative to address the gender imbalance in the areas of Science, Technology, Engineering, Mathematics and Medicine (STEMM). It evolved from work between the Athena Project and the Scientific Women&rsquo;s Academic Network (SWAN) and has a central charter that is owned and operated by the <a title="Equality Challenge Unit" href="http://www.ecu.ac.uk/" target="_blank">Equality Challenge Unit (ECU)</a>.</p>
<h2>What does the Athena SWAN initiative mean for me?</h2>
<div class="image_container right" style="width: 200px;"><a title="Athena SWAN" href="http://www.ecu.ac.uk/equality-charter-marks/athena-swan/" target="_blank"><img src="/_asset/image/bronze-logo.png/fit/200/200" alt="Bronze logo" /></a></div>
<p>The University and all of its individual divisions and departments, including RDM, are fully committed to implementing the Athena SWAN initiative. As a result of this, the University, RDM and its constituent divisions all have Bronze awards and RDM is actively working towards a Silver award.</p>
<h2>What's happening next?</h2>
<p>As the divisions within RDM implement those actions identified in their Bronze applications they will build and develop on these, forming the basis of a RDM Silver award application. This will include a further staff questionnaire to identify priority areas for action.&nbsp;A single&nbsp;application will be made by RDM, and if awarded, the Silver award status will apply to all of the divisions within RDM. The challenge will then be to push on for a Gold award and achieve the very best for our staff.</p>
<p>To achieve this each division within RDM has a&nbsp;<a href="/athena-swan-assessment-teams" target="_self">Athena SWAN Self-Assessment Team</a>&nbsp;that is responsible for implementing actions locally. There is also an <a href="/athena-swan-assessment-teams" target="_self">RDM&nbsp;Athena SWAN Steering Group</a>&nbsp;that helps to instigate and co-ordinate Athena SWAN action plans across the whole of RDM.</p>
<h2>Where can I go to find more information?</h2>
<p>Information regarding the Athena SWAN initiative can be found on <a title="Athena SWAN" href="http://www.ecu.ac.uk/equality-charter-marks/athena-swan/" target="_blank">their webpage</a>.</p>
<p>The latest Athena SWAN news can be found at our dedicated <a title="Athena SWAN News" href="/athena-swan-news" target="_self">Athena SWAN news webpage</a>.</p>
<p>The <a href="http://www.admin.ox.ac.uk/eop/gender/athenaswan/" target="_blank">University has a set of pages</a> dedicated to Athena SWAN, with information regarding the Medical Sciences Division Athena SWAN response available through <a title="Medsci newsletters" href="http://www.medsci.ox.ac.uk/newsletters" target="_blank">their newsletters</a>.</p>
<p>If you should have any further queries regarding Athena SWAN in your division, <a title="Key contacts in your RDM Division" href="/key-contacts-in-your-rdm-division" target="_self">your admin team</a>&nbsp;will be able to provide you with more information.&nbsp;</p></div>
